          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-5">
            <h3 style="font-weight:200; margin-bottom:20px;">1. Prepare Project and Install</h3>
            <h4 style="font-weight:400; color:#454545; margin-bottom:30px;">WE HAVE 2 WAYS TO PREPARE AND INSTALL.</h4>
            <p style="color: #454545;">
            	summer-mvc can be run on any Nodejs projects.
            	Create project and Initialize project.
            	And install summer-mvc using <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/summer-mvc">NPM</a> (Nodejs Package Moduler).
            	If you want to install using binary, please download binary files and exracte it under {user-project}/node_modules/summer-mvc.
            </p>
            <button class="btn_important" onclick="javascript:location.href = '/getting-started#get_summer_mvc'">Get summer-mvc</button>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lo-1 col-md-1 col-sm-1"></div>
        </div>

        <center><img style="margin-top:20px; margin-bottom:20px;" src="/arrow_dn_left.png"></center>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lo-1 col-md-1 col-sm-1"></div>
          <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-5">
            <h3 style="font-weight:200; margin-bottom:20px;">2. Write 1 line and Execute</h3>
            <h4 style="font-weight:400; color:#454545; margin-bottom:30px; color: #454545">DURING INITIAL RUNNING TIME,<br> BUILD & CREATE APPLICATION ARCHITECTURE.</h4>
            <p style="color: #454545;">
            	<code style="font-size: 1.2em">const mvc = require( "summer-mvc" );</code> <br>
            	This only one line of code is required for executing summer-mvc.
            	As controlling HTTP req/res is event-driven, you just add that code and wait until client send a signal.
            	If your project is under first executed with summer-mvc, your project will be transformed as summer-mvc architecture.
            </p>
            <button class="btn_important" onclick="javascript:location.href='/getting-started#initializing'">Initializing</button>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-5">
            <center><img style="width:60%; margin-top:20px;" src="/execution.png" /></center>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lo-1 col-md-1 col-sm-1"></div>
        </div>

        <center><img style="margin-top:20px; margin-bottom:20px;" src="/arrow_dn_right.png"></center>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lo-1 col-md-1 col-sm-1"></div>
          <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-5">
            <center><img style="width:80%; margin-top: 20px;" src="/write_code.png" /></center>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5 col-sm-5">
            <h3 style="font-weight:200; margin-bottom: 20px;">3. Implement Your Business Logic</h3>
            <h4 style="font-weight:400; color:#454545; margin-bottom: 30px; color: #454545">FOCUS YOUR TAKS. IMPLEMENT BUSINESS REQUIRE.</h4>
            <p style="color: #454545;">
            	Now, your job is that write your business codes.
            	Just implement controllers, models and views.
       			As summer-mvc control all other things, you can only focus your requirements.
       			Fast developement speed comes from that.
            </p>
            <button class="btn_important" onclick="javascript:location.href='/getting-started#create_application'">Create Application</button>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lo-1 col-md-1 col-sm-1"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
